1
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:39,033
<i>What did you say to Timo
after I left?</i>

2
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:40,267
<i> What are you implying?</i>

3
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,400
<i> I coached him?</i>

4
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,800
<i>Why didn't he say it
in his first statement?</i>

5
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:45,100
<i> Prepare yourself.</i>

6
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:47,733
<i>We're filing charges
against Coleen.</i>

7
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:48,700
<i> Who are you?</i>

8
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:49,800
<i> I'm Coleen's mother.</i>

9
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:50,867
<i> I don't want to talk to you.</i>

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,700
<i> How much did Hazel pay you?</i>

11
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:54,433
<i> Timo is lying.</i>

12
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:56,433
<i>He couldn't even look me
straight in the eye.</i>

13
00:00:56,567 --> 00:00:59,367
<i>We just got word
from the Fiscal's office.</i>

14
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:02,567
<i>Hazel has officially filed
the case against Coleen.</i>

15
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:03,533
<i> Come on.</i>

16
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:04,800
<i> Joel, everyone, go on and eat.</i>

17
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:05,733
<i> Mom, Dad...</i>

18
00:01:05,867 --> 00:01:08,233
<i>is there something
you want to say?</i>

19
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,100
<i>Did Hazel file a case
against me?</i>

20
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:12,100
<i>We are filing a complaint
for murder</i>

21
00:01:12,233 --> 00:01:16,467
<i>under Article 248
of the Revised Penal Code.</i>

22
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:18,800
<i> There was evident malice.</i>

23
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:20,500
<i> The act was deliberate.</i>

24
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:21,800
<i> She did it on purpose.</i>

25
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:24,400
<i> She meant to kill Jessica.</i>

26
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:26,967
<i>Fiscal, I did not push Jessica.</i>

27
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:29,667
<i>We will file
our counter-affidavit.</i>

28
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,367
<i> See you in court.</i>

29
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,667
<i>That is, if your conscience
can handle it.</i>

30
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:38,033
<i>I hope Jessica haunts
your sleep every night.</i>

31
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:40,033
<i> Call an ambulance!</i>

32
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,367
<i>You're the reason Jessica died.</i>

33
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,533
<i> You pushed her.</i>

34
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:45,233
<i> Coleen!</i>

35
00:01:47,867 --> 00:01:48,533
<i> Coleen!</i>

36
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:49,333
<i> What are you doing?</i>

37
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:50,300
<i> Give me that!</i>

38
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:51,600
<i> What were you thinking?</i>

39
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:55,967
<i>I just wanted to sleep
peacefully.</i>

40
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:59,700
<i>Ever since Jessica died,
I've lost my peace of mind.</i>

41
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:04,300
<i>If I get jailed, will that
lessen the guilt I'm carrying?</i>

42
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,233
<i> I'm here.</i>

43
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:07,700
<i> We'll help you.</i>

44
00:02:07,833 --> 00:02:09,367
<i> We'll stay by your side.</i>

45
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,033
<i> You'll get through this.</i>

46
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:13,300
<i>We'll get through this together.</i>

47
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:23,000
How's Coleen?

48
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:27,600
She fell asleep
after having dinner.

49
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,867
I'll just get some water.

50
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,467
And then I'll stay with her.

51
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,000
I'll sleep in her room for now.

52
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,733
How about you?
How are you feeling?

53
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:43,633
Somehow, I feel relieved.

54
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:53,833
Our youngest made a promise that
she'll take care of herself.

55
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,500
Manuel, can I really be
completely at ease?

56
00:02:57,633 --> 00:02:59,700
What about tomorrow?

57
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:00,933
The day after next?

58
00:03:02,667 --> 00:03:05,533
I'll be worrying about
Coleen every minute.

59
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:10,233
Felma, we both feel the same.

60
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:14,067
I'm also worried
about our youngest.

61
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,900
I've already lost Jessica.

62
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:22,700
I don't know if I can still bear
it if I also lose Coleen.

63
00:03:23,633 --> 00:03:26,333
Don't say something like that.

64
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:28,567
It would kill me, Manuel.

65
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:31,100
Felma, we won't let that happen.

66
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:34,767
We'll help each other.

67
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,233
Felma.

68
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:38,533
Felma, we'll hold on
to Coleen's promise

69
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:40,933
that she will never hurt
herself.

70
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,867
And we'll hold on
to God's promise

71
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,600
that He will never abandon us.

72
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:48,633
Our children were His
before they ever became ours.

73
00:03:48,767 --> 00:03:51,633
I'm sure he will
take care of Coleen.

74
00:03:51,767 --> 00:03:53,067
Thank you, Manuel.

75
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:59,833
Having you here
and comforting me means a lot.

76
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,067
Felma, we're in this
battle together.

77
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,533
We'll take this on
one day at a time.

78
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:07,400
One step at a time.

79
00:04:07,533 --> 00:04:09,700
Until we get through it.

80
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,300
<i> Hazel!</i>

81
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,967
Hazel!

82
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:29,633
<i> Hazel!</i>

83
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,600
<i> Hazel!</i>

84
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:34,800
<i> Friend! Open the door!</i>

85
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:35,667
<i> Hazel!</i>

86
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:39,067
<i> Friend!</i>

87
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,633
<i> Hazel!</i>

88
00:04:40,767 --> 00:04:41,300
<i> Hazel!</i>

89
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:42,567
It's me, Alice!

90
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:48,167
Oh my God.

91
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:56,267
What happened to you?

92
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,133
<i> Look at this place.</i>

93
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:07,833
This isn't you.

94
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:09,933
You hate being messy.
What's gotten into you?

95
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:13,167
Come here.

96
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:14,867
Let's drink.

97
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:20,567
Is this why you didn't answer
my texts and calls?

98
00:05:22,567 --> 00:05:24,900
Because you've drowned
yourself in alcohol?

99
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:27,200
Is this what you've been eating
for the past three days?

100
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:32,200
Friend, what you're doing
isn't healthy.

101
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:34,033
Can't I break the rules?

102
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:37,900
Wait.

103
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:39,800
I'll get some more. Let's drink.

104
00:05:55,733 --> 00:05:56,700
Here.

105
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:04,500
Have a drink.

106
00:06:04,633 --> 00:06:06,933
Okay, you're now grieving.

107
00:06:08,533 --> 00:06:10,133
Finally, I get it, friend.

108
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:14,667
You can't understand.

109
00:06:16,567 --> 00:06:17,100
Because...

110
00:06:19,233 --> 00:06:20,567
Because you don't have a child.

111
00:06:25,533 --> 00:06:27,100
You didn't lose a child.

112
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,800
Yes, maybe I don't understand.

113
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:42,233
But it pains me because
I care about you as a friend.

114
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:46,200
And as Jessica's godmother.

115
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:47,733
It's only right that you grieve

116
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:50,767
for what happened
to my goddaughter.

117
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,733
But don't let it get to the
point where you're depressed

118
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:54,700
and neglecting yourself.

119
00:06:56,633 --> 00:06:59,133
Don't stay there, friend.

120
00:06:59,267 --> 00:07:01,600
Get up and fight again.

121
00:07:05,033 --> 00:07:07,833
Anyway, go on.

122
00:07:07,967 --> 00:07:09,000
Take a bath.

123
00:07:09,133 --> 00:07:11,367
Change your clothes.
We're going out.

124
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:12,833
We'll eat good food.

125
00:07:12,967 --> 00:07:15,133
It's on me, friend.

126
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:17,133
Friend, come on.

127
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:33,967
Dear, please try this.

128
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,600
Is it too sweet or just right?

129
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:39,700
- It's good, Mom.
- Good?

130
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:40,867
Okay.

131
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,067
That's yours, wait.

132
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,067
Who wants some juice?

133
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:43,967
Would you like some, Manuel?

134
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:47,167
Coleen, look.

135
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,800
We even prepared all
your favorite ingredients

136
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:52,167
for the hotpot.

137
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:53,233
You love this, right?

138
00:07:53,367 --> 00:07:54,733
Thank you.

139
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:55,433
Dear, you want dessert?

140
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:56,300
Ice cream?

141
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:57,267
I can get some later.
Do you want?

142
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,333
- I'll go.
- No, let me.

143
00:07:58,467 --> 00:08:00,800
- No, let me.
- No. Joel, Jeffrey, t's okay.

144
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:01,700
Thank you.

145
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:02,900
Are you sure?

146
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:05,467
Coleen, do you want me to peel
your favorite orange?

147
00:08:07,367 --> 00:08:09,667
Dad...

148
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,467
Thank you, everyone,
for all the effort.

149
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,667
For trying to make me
feel better.

150
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,933
Sweetie, that's nothing yet.

151
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:17,733
I know what you love.

152
00:08:17,867 --> 00:08:19,333
Those viral dance videos.

153
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:20,767
- Like this.
- Wow.

154
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:26,967
I think that isn't enough yet.

155
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,367
Wait for it.

156
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,767
We have a dance group.

157
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:32,033
We'll dance on your birthday.

158
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,400
And dance moves like this.

159
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:35,300
It looks like...

160
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,667
And this...

161
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:39,567
Sir Manuel, is this okay?

162
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,100
Didang, come on.

163
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:46,333
That will make you walk again.

164
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:07,833
Hazel!

165
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:16,033
If you're only going to fight me
over what I did to your child,

166
00:09:16,167 --> 00:09:19,900
you're just wasting your breath
and my time.

167
00:09:20,033 --> 00:09:22,267
There's nothing we can do.

168
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,900
The choice is in the hands
of the prosecutor.

169
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:27,633
But there's one thing
I'll make sure of.

170
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,000
Your child will face
criminal charges.

171
00:09:30,133 --> 00:09:31,700
Why are you so sure?

172
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,600
Why?

173
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:42,267
Has your brain gone numb?

174
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:45,233
The driver has already
testified, remember?

175
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:49,033
He clearly saw
when your child pushed mine.

176
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,233
If he was really telling
the truth,

177
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:54,200
then he should've said it
in his first statement.

178
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:56,767
But he only added that detail.

179
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,700
You probably did something.

180
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:00,233
That's why he expanded
his statement.

181
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,100
What could I even do?

182
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:08,500
Maybe you paid the driver.

183
00:10:08,633 --> 00:10:10,667
You told him to lie.

184
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,467
You used your connections.

185
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,600
You talked to your lawyer.

186
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:14,933
The prosecutor.

187
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,967
You're the one who knows
what you did, Hazel.

188
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:17,633
So tell me.

189
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:20,300
Tell me the truth!

190
00:10:20,433 --> 00:10:23,067
Is that how low you see me?

191
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,167
You can't blame my dad.

192
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:28,700
He's just going by
your track record.

193
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,533
Excuse me?

194
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:32,200
Am I talking to you?

195
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:33,767
Jeff, please give us a minute.

196
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:43,267
Your firstborn is rude.

197
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,767
He has a point, Hazel.

198
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:47,833
With all your sins, I wouldn't
be surprised in the least

199
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:50,933
if you went out of your way
to frame Coleen.

200
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,267
And Coleen is perfect?

201
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,233
Doesn't she make mistakes?

202
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:59,233
How many times did she hurt
and fight Jessica?

203
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:02,200
Isn't it possible that
she made a mistake again?

204
00:11:04,867 --> 00:11:06,133
She pushed Jessica.

205
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,600
That's why my daughter got hit
and died.

206
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:12,433
Whether she did it
on purpose or not.

207
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:19,767
Yes, I did so many wrong things.

208
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:25,400
But isn't it possible that
this time I'm telling the truth?

209
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:28,267
That I have nothing to do
with the driver's statement?

210
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:34,533
I only want to give justice
to our daughter's death.

211
00:11:36,867 --> 00:11:38,300
Whether it's the driver...

212
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,700
Coleen, or someone else.

213
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:44,100
That's it.

214
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:47,233
Hazel, honestly...

215
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:52,400
I really want to give justice
to what happened to Jessica.

216
00:11:52,533 --> 00:11:56,167
But if you see
Coleen's condition,

217
00:11:56,300 --> 00:12:00,000
you'll understand why
I'm fighting for her.

218
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:02,267
Hazel, you're a mother, too.

219
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:05,233
You know what I mean.

220
00:12:05,367 --> 00:12:10,867
I don't know how I can be
called a mother now

221
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,267
that I've lost my one
and only child.

222
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:16,800
I don't know what to do anymore.

223
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:21,633
I don't know what to think.

224
00:12:21,767 --> 00:12:23,767
Think of Jessica.

225
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:28,933
Manuel, only think of her.

226
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:32,167
The justice she needs.

227
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:35,067
Something she deserves.

228
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,533
Think about that.

229
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:39,633
Please?

230
00:12:39,767 --> 00:12:43,667
Don't manipulate me
to stop pinning it on Coleen.

231
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:47,867
Let the prosecutor
and the court decide

232
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,000
whether or not she's accountable
under the law.

233
00:12:51,167 --> 00:12:51,867
Please?

234
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:31,733
Seriously, Jeffrey.

235
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:33,667
Why did you go to Hazel again?

236
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:37,567
Dad wanted to talk
to Hazel, Mom.

237
00:13:39,767 --> 00:13:42,167
Was it about Coleen again?

238
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:44,300
Did he beg for your sister
again?

239
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:47,633
He hasn't learn his lesson.

240
00:13:47,767 --> 00:13:49,267
And you.

241
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,533
You know how stubborn
that woman is.

242
00:13:51,667 --> 00:13:54,133
And you brought
your father to her?

243
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:57,400
Mom, you know I can't
refuse dad right now.

244
00:13:57,533 --> 00:14:02,233
So did anything happen
during their talk?

245
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:06,233
Or did that Hazel woman
attack him again?

246
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:08,700
I didn't hear them.

247
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:11,533
Dad asked me to leave.

248
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:12,967
Actually, it didn't look
like they were fighting.

249
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:14,733
It kind of looked like
they were getting along.

250
00:14:14,867 --> 00:14:15,767
They seemed to get along.

251
00:14:18,267 --> 00:14:19,300
Getting along?

252
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:22,100
I don't know, Mom.

253
00:14:22,233 --> 00:14:25,333
But when we went home,
dad seemed okay.

254
00:14:37,067 --> 00:14:37,933
So, Attorney...

255
00:14:39,867 --> 00:14:41,800
When will the prosecutor's
decision come out?

256
00:14:46,367 --> 00:14:49,400
Well, it hasn't come out yet.

257
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:52,867
I'm asking when.

258
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,767
Mrs. Cruz, we need
to be patient.

259
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:03,800
We can't rush the fiscal.

260
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:09,900
Attorney, I don't have
much patience left.

261
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:14,567
So if I were you, I'd call my
contact in that fiscal's office.

262
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,400
So we'd know.

263
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:18,400
And give me some good news.

264
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:24,600
Mrs. Cruz, I think you
should have some sweets.

265
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:27,467
So you can show some sweetness.

266
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,367
Felma, you've been quiet
since earlier.

267
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,267
So you met with Hazel.

268
00:16:03,533 --> 00:16:08,967
I know I have no right to demand
that you ask my permission.

269
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:12,367
But if Coleen has something
to do with it,

270
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:14,767
you should've let me know.

271
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:17,867
I don't want to add
to your concerns.

272
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,600
How would that even add up?

273
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:22,300
I was suspicious that
Hazel did something.

274
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:24,733
That's why the driver made
an additional statement.

275
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:27,967
But I didn't have any proof.

276
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:30,533
So I went to talk to her.

277
00:16:30,667 --> 00:16:32,300
Did she confess?

278
00:16:32,433 --> 00:16:34,000
Of course, she didn't.

279
00:16:34,133 --> 00:16:36,300
I've always suspected it.

280
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:39,633
That woman has likely
done something.

281
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:43,033
But Hazel could be right.

282
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:48,000
What if the driver really
saw Coleen push Jessica?

283
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:52,533
Manuel, has that woman
brainwashed you?

284
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:53,733
No.

285
00:16:53,867 --> 00:16:54,567
It's not like that.

286
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:56,033
My only point is,

287
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:58,733
we can't control
the driver's perspective.

288
00:16:58,867 --> 00:17:01,967
What if he really assumes
that Coleen pushed Jessica?

289
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,300
Right?

290
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:09,500
What we should do is to think
of a way to prove it wrong.

291
00:17:09,633 --> 00:17:12,567
Coleen's testimony is enough.

292
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:15,700
If she said she didn't
push Jessica,

293
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:17,167
then that's the truth!

294
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:18,333
And nothing else!

295
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:20,267
Yes, I also believe her.

296
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:23,267
Really, Manuel?

297
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:26,267
You changed your mind

298
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,867
- after meeting with Hazel!
- No. Felma!

299
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,300
Felma, nothing has changed.

300
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:36,467
My only point is,
maybe we shouldn't accuse Hazel.

301
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:39,033
She lost a child.

302
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:42,300
She wants nothing
but to get justice for Jessica.

303
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:45,167
That's what I also want
for Coleen!

304
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,533
For her to be given justice

305
00:17:47,667 --> 00:17:49,133
against the accusation
of that woman.

306
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,167
That's also what I want.

307
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:54,633
Are you sure, Manuel?

308
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:56,200
Maybe you're just saying that.

309
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:59,400
But your heart says otherwise.

310
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,767
<i> Felma?</i>

311
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:17,067
Felma.

312
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,500
Andeng told me to bring this.

313
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:22,433
Here's the menu
for Joel's party.

314
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:24,200
Maybe you have some ideas?

315
00:18:25,233 --> 00:18:26,167
Felma?

316
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:31,533
Hey, what happened?

317
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:36,700
It's Manuel.

318
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:40,333
He talked with Hazel
about Coleen.

319
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:41,567
He was making that woman
admit what she did.

320
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:52,000
That made the driver testify
against Coleen pushing Jessica.

321
00:18:52,133 --> 00:18:55,200
That's possible.

322
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:56,233
That's the case.

323
00:18:57,767 --> 00:19:03,167
But it seems like Manuel
is taking Hazel's side.

324
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:06,567
He seems to believe that
what happened to Jessica

325
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,133
was Coleen's fault.

326
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:13,700
Bro, it's not like
I believe Hazel.

327
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,233
But she seems to have a point.

328
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,733
What if the driver
really assumes

329
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,533
that Coleen pushed Jessica?

330
00:19:22,933 --> 00:19:24,467
You know what, Bro?

331
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,700
I understand you.

332
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:27,333
I know.

333
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,833
But Felma doesn't understand me.

334
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:33,267
What Manuel told me was clear.

335
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:43,867
But it seems more obvious to me
that Hazel did something

336
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,133
to influence the driver.

337
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:47,833
Manuel didn't understand that.

338
00:19:47,967 --> 00:19:51,500
Manuel understands that.

339
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:53,933
He didn't just witness it.

340
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:59,533
He experienced
her wife's craziness.

341
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:04,100
Maybe he's just not
pushing it for now.

342
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:06,667
So he's siding
with that woman now?

343
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,933
Just recently,

344
00:20:10,067 --> 00:20:16,700
he promised me that we'd face
this trial together.

345
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:19,567
Bro, there's probably nothing
wrong with comforting Hazel,

346
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:20,733
right?

347
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:25,733
I know, she wasn't a good wife
and mother.

348
00:20:25,867 --> 00:20:28,400
But she's still
Jessica's mother.

349
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:29,300
And I'm the father.

350
00:20:31,133 --> 00:20:34,667
It shouldn't be wrong for us
to grieve as parents.

351
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,733
You know what, Bro?

352
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:40,933
Just be more understanding
with Felma.

353
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:44,200
What she's going through
right now is not easy.

354
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:46,833
Seeing her child
being accused.

355
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:47,733
And me?

356
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,967
I'm the father of the child
being accused.

357
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:55,200
I've already lost a child.

358
00:20:55,333 --> 00:20:58,067
And the other one
is being accused of a crime.

359
00:20:58,200 --> 00:21:00,400
Bro, I'm so stuck between
a rock and a hard place.

360
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:05,200
Felma, don't you think what
you're feeling right now

361
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,233
is jealousy?

362
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:15,100
Paz, I don't have time
to get jealous.

363
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:17,333
I'm not thinking about that.

364
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:26,033
My only point is, yes,
we should grieve for Jessica.

365
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:35,767
But it's wrong that Manuel
is letting Hazel and that driver

366
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:37,533
pin it on my daughter.

367
00:21:39,533 --> 00:21:44,933
Coleen shouldn't be charged
with a crime she didn't commit.

368
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:47,833
She can't go to jail.

369
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:49,567
Do you understand that?

370
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:52,700
She can't go to jail.

371
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:58,433
If that happens, it's the same
as killing my daughter!

372
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:05,467
It's the same as killing
my daughter.

373
00:22:12,767 --> 00:22:15,400
We need Manuel now.

374
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:17,133
We need him now.

375
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:22,167
Could the same thing happen
all over again?

376
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,933
That he won't keep
his promise again!

377
00:22:29,533 --> 00:22:31,533
And he'll abandon us once more!

378
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,433
I don't want that to happen
to my daughter?

379
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:57,200
I don't want that.

380
00:22:58,367 --> 00:23:03,500
Happy birthday to you!

381
00:23:03,933 --> 00:23:05,000
Wish, wish, wish!

382
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:11,600
Yes!

383
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:13,900
Thank you, everyone.

384
00:23:14,033 --> 00:23:16,167
This means a lot to me.

385
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:17,167
Despite the...

386
00:23:20,467 --> 00:23:23,967
I'm happy knowing that you want
to celebrate with me.

387
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:25,367
I don't have my family here,

388
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:28,300
but you didn't let me feel
I'm alone.

389
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:32,233
So it's already the best gift.

390
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:33,333
So thank you so much.

391
00:23:33,467 --> 00:23:35,200
<i> There we go!</i>

392
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:36,667
<i>You're not a stranger to us,
Bro.</i>

393
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:37,733
You're part of the family.

394
00:23:37,867 --> 00:23:39,800
Because Andrea's
your girlfriend now, right?

395
00:23:39,933 --> 00:23:40,967
What?

396
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:44,200
- Yes, he's Andeng's boyfriend!
- Okay!

397
00:23:44,333 --> 00:23:45,700
- You wish!
- You wish?

398
00:23:45,833 --> 00:23:47,200
Good thing we celebrated here.

399
00:23:47,333 --> 00:23:49,700
Wait. Are you expecting guests?

400
00:23:49,833 --> 00:23:51,200
No. I'm not.

401
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:53,667
Let's eat! Let's eat!
Let's eat! Let's eat!

402
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:54,300
Come on, let's eat.

403
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:56,633
Let's go, Dad.

404
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,800
Manuel, here.

405
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,300
Joel.

406
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:01,900
Yes, go.

407
00:24:02,033 --> 00:24:02,700
Here.

408
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,567
Ma'am Felma.

409
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:05,433
<i> Good day.</i>

410
00:24:10,867 --> 00:24:12,367
Good day, too.

411
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:14,567
How can we assist you?

412
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,233
Is Coleen Ruiz Cruz here?

413
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:19,600
What do you need
from my daughter?

414
00:24:21,067 --> 00:24:23,167
That's a warrant of arrest.

415
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:25,533
We're taking your daughter
into custody.

416
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:26,200
What?

417
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:42,967
That's her!

418
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:43,967
That's her!

419
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:45,567
She's the one
who pushed Jessica!

420
00:24:45,700 --> 00:24:46,500
It was your fault!

421
00:24:46,633 --> 00:24:47,500
I didn't push her!

422
00:24:47,633 --> 00:24:48,467
It was your fault!

423
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,867
- I didn't push her!
- It was you!

424
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:51,100
It was really you!

425
00:24:51,233 --> 00:24:54,567
Mrs. Cruz, it's not that
I want to rain on your parade.

426
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:57,267
But the fight has just started.

427
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,533
But you'll do everything, right?

428
00:24:59,667 --> 00:25:01,933
To keep Coleen
from getting out of prison.

429
00:25:04,833 --> 00:25:06,800
Bro, your lawyer
is there already, right?

430
00:25:06,933 --> 00:25:07,800
He'll fix everything.

431
00:25:07,933 --> 00:25:10,233
The truth will come out.

432
00:25:10,367 --> 00:25:12,467
Coleen will be acquitted.

433
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,733
For Coleen.
